abstract: South Korean and U.S. special forces troops recently conducted drills simulating the infiltration of an enemy facility, U.S. military photos seen by Reuters on Monday show, as tensions with North Korea ratchet up ahead of a year-end deadline.
snippet: South Korean and U.S. special forces troops recently conducted drills simulating the infiltration of an enemy facility, U.S. military photos seen by Reuters on Monday show, as tensions with North Korea ratchet up ahead of a year-end deadline.
lead_paragraph: SEOUL — South Korean and U.S. special forces troops recently conducted drills simulating the infiltration of an enemy facility, U.S. military photos seen by Reuters on Monday show, as tensions with North Korea ratchet up ahead of a year-end deadline.
headline_main: South Korea, U.S. Commandos Practice Raiding Enemy Facility as North Korea Tensions Rise
headline_print_headline: South Korea, U.S. Commandos Practice Raiding Enemy Facility as North Korea Tensions Rise

abstract: Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell said on Monday that Republicans were not opposed to hearing witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
snippet: Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell said on Monday that Republicans were not opposed to hearing witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell said on Monday that Republicans were not opposed to hearing witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
headline_main: McConnell Says Senate Republicans Have Not Ruled Out Witnesses in Trump Impeachment Trial
headline_print_headline: McConnell Says Senate Republicans Have Not Ruled Out Witnesses in Trump Impeachment Trial

abstract: World stocks hovered near record highs and currency markets were little changed on Monday as trading dwindled before the Christmas holiday and investors looked with confidence toward the new year.
snippet: World stocks hovered near record highs and currency markets were little changed on Monday as trading dwindled before the Christmas holiday and investors looked with confidence toward the new year.
lead_paragraph: MILAN — World stocks hovered near record highs and currency markets were little changed on Monday as trading dwindled before the Christmas holiday and investors looked with confidence toward the new year.
headline_main: Global Shares Hover Near Record High as Year Draws to Close
headline_print_headline: Global Shares Hover Near Record High as Year Draws to Close

abstract: Russia, Poland, Christmas market: Here’s what you need to know.
snippet: Russia, Poland, Christmas market: Here’s what you need to know.
lead_paragraph: North Korea has promised a “Christmas gift” to the United States if no progress is made on lifting sanctions. That may be shorthand for a test of an intercontinental ballistic missile — and it could produce a particularly dire cycle of crisis.
